  <body>
      <h2>GUIs</h2>

      <p>There are several ways to add interactivity to an Rpad page.
      From simplest to complex, some possibilities are:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><em>Rpad GUI tools --</em> Through the Rpad menu, you can
        add links, checkboxes, and radio buttons (if the GUI is enabled).</li>

        <li><em>Copy and paste</em> -- You can paste widgets from other
        web pages or other web-page design programs.</li>

        <li><em>Handmade</em> -- You can hand enter the html or use
        other html design programs to generate more complex widgets,
        including javascript if needed.</li>

        <li><em>R generation --</em> For more complex entries or when
        the gui element is based on server-side data, it is easier to
        generate the GUI elements on the server.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>The basic GUI elements that are "named" are translated into
      variables with the same name in R. Here are some basic elements:</p>
<form>
      <p class="c1"><span contenteditable="false"><input type=
      "checkbox" name="isPepperoni"></span>Pepperoni <span
      contenteditable="false"><input type="checkbox" name=
      "isSausage"></span>Sausage <span contenteditable="false"><input
      type="checkbox" checked="true" name="isExtraCheese"></span>Extra
      cheese <span contenteditable="false"><input type="checkbox"
      checked="true" name="isMushrooms"></span>Mushrooms <span
      contenteditable="false"><input type="checkbox" checked="true"
      name="isPeppers"></span>Peppers <span contenteditable=
      "false"><input type="checkbox" name="isOnions"></span>Onions</p>

      <p><span contenteditable="false"><select name="browserDropdown">
        <option>
          Internet Explorer
        </option>

        <option>
          Netscape Navigator
        </option>
      </select></span></p>

      <p><span contenteditable="false"><input class="Rpad_input" name=
      "favoriteNumber" rpadtype="Rvariable" value="44"></span>
      Favorite number</p>

      <p><span contenteditable="false"><input onclick=
      "javascript:rpad.calculatePage()" value="Calculate" type=
      "button"></span> (This button just does the same as F9 or the
      Calculate menu item.)</p>
</form>

      <p>Here is a dropdown list generated by R:</p>

      <pre dojoType="Rpad" rpadRun="init">
HTMLon() # switch to html mode
data(state)
HTMLselect("favoriteAmericanState", state.name) # generate the select box
      </pre>

      <p>After fiddling with some of the inputs, hit F9 or the
      calculate button and see that the following outputs change:</p>

      <pre dojoType="Rpad">
cat("isPepperoni =",isPepperoni,"\n")
cat("browserDropdown =",browserDropdown,"\n")
cat("favoriteNumber =",favoriteNumber,"\n")
cat("favoriteAmericanState =",favoriteAmericanState,"\n")
      </pre>



</span>

